COMMUNITY LICENSE & QFDM ROYALTY TERMS
--------------------------------------

The Software is available under a dual model — a free open-source community license for the software, and royalty-based terms for any commercial exploitation of the patented QFDM system:

  1. COMMUNITY LICENSE (Open Core)
     The open-source components of this Software are available under the GNU Affero General Public License v3 (AGPLv3) for up to nine (9) nodes, free of charge, for non-commercial, community, home lab, and educational use. See the LICENSE-AGPL file or https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html.

  2. COMMERCIAL USE — QFDM ROYALTY FEES
     Home Lab enthusiasts are encouraged to grow their deployments. Once you reach ten (10) or more nodes, you become eligible to apply for integration into the QFDM Backend Infrastructure as a compensated provider, earning real money for your room, energy, and maintenance contributions — subject to meeting basic
     requirements such as proof of electricity bill origin, physical safety compliance, and secured hardware access.

     Commercial exploitation of the QFDM system is NOT a software license and is NOT a fee for any software service rendered to the public. It is the exercise of rights under Patent NC2025/0012723, and the amounts payable are ROYALTY FEES — consideration paid to the patent holder, Grupo 3P1 Colombia, for the right to use and exploit the patented QFDM (Quantized Fractional Distribution and Management System) invention.

     QFDM Royalty Fees are payable for any commercial exploitation of the patented QFDM system, including:
       - Each Codec Terminal connecting to the QFDM network.
       - Deployments of ten (10) or more nodes.
       - Hosting the service as a third-party provider.
       - Embedding the patented QFDM technology in proprietary products.
       - Any use that directly or indirectly generates revenue.
       *QFDM Royalty Fees are paid as patent royalties and may be accompanied by patent grants, warranties, support, and indemnification.


